  "observations": [
    "The unchanged adapter built and produced identical CPU and GPU fingerprints on both official MLX releases.",
    "The Metal Float16 output exactly matched the official MLX Examples oracle. The CPU Float32 output matched within normal last-bit reduction differences.",
    "A source-built CPU Float16 convolution diverged at the first convolution even though the log-Mel input matched. The adapter therefore follows MLX Whisper's supported Float32 CPU path and retains Float16 on Metal.",
    "NPY loading evaluates on CPU; GPU sessions must explicitly materialize weights on CPU and copy them to Metal.",
    "MLX caches Metal kernels and buffers across an encode call. The session destroy path deletes owned arrays and clears the MLX cache; all three create/run/destroy cycles completed.",
    "The global MLX default device makes the current adapter process-serialized. The C ABI mutex prevents cross-session device races.",
    "An executable-relative RPATH and a colocated mlx.metallib are required at runtime.",
    "This is the complete Whisper tiny audio encoder on real speech, not a decoder or transcription-quality result."
